5. Exception Scenarios

The system must handle:

Double booking
Doctor unavailable
Clinic holiday
Payment failure
SMS failure
Email failure
Lab upload failure
Report correction
Patient no show
Doctor absence
Internet interruption
Session timeout
6. Notifications

The system should notify users for:

Patient

Appointment confirmation
Reminder
Cancellation
Lab report ready
Payment success
Follow-up reminder

Doctor

New appointment
Cancellation
Lab report ready

Reception

Walk-in
Queue updates
Payment pending
7. Dashboard Updates

After every important event, all relevant dashboards should reflect the latest data immediately.

Example:

Patient books appointment

↓

Patient Dashboard

↓

Doctor Dashboard

↓

Reception Dashboard

↓

Calendar

↓

Analytics

↓

Notification Queue

8. Business Rules

Every workflow must:

Validate authentication.
Validate tenant.
Validate permissions.
Create audit logs.
Generate notifications.
Update dashboards.
Maintain data consistency.
9. Future Use Cases

These workflows will be added in later releases:

Insurance Claims
Inventory Replenishment
Pharmacy Dispensing
AI Medical Assistant
Voice Consultation Notes
Telemedicine
Marketing Campaigns
CRM
Multi-Branch Clinics
Corporate Health Programs
Document Summary

This document describes how Clinora works from the user's perspective. It focuses on business workflows rather than technical implementation. Each approved use case will later be translated into Product Requirements Documents (PRDs), UI wireframes, APIs, database changes, Jira stories, and test cases.
